	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'd personally suggest you head on over to Lake Rathetear.&nbsp;&nbsp;You can solo or group there for the Aviak Guards.  They aren't that tough, sometimes drop bronze, and are great experience.  With your lull song, you can easily break the spawn.  Once you hit 18, you can do the all-instrument attack (Denon's Disruptive Discord, Chords of Discordance, and Hymn of Restoriation, all while twisting instruments) to bring them to their knees.  Once past 18, I'm sure you can solo them easily, and should be able to take a camp of 2 or 3 guards, just remember to lull.  With ease, this should bring you to 22 or 23.  From there, you can perform for groups in Cazic Thule or the Southern Karanas, it's up to you.<br>&nbsp;<br>Ensis Arament</td></tr>
